sections.History:
===Background===
According to legend, the Nightfort served as the seat of the [[Night's King]], who had been seduced by a [[Night's Queen|woman]] from [[beyond the Wall]]. He brought her back to the Nightfort and performed dark sacrifices to the [[White Walkers]]. However, he was defeated by the [[King in the North]] [[Brandon Stark (the Breaker)|Brandon the Breaker]] and the [[King-beyond-the-Wall]] [[Joramun]] who joined forces to destroy him.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Night's Watch (Histories &amp; Lore)]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 3]]===
The Nightfort, although ruined, contains a secret passage under the Wall, which leads to a well up inside the castle. [[Samwell Tarly]] tells [[Gilly]] about it, as he read it in a book.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Rains of Castamere (episode)|The Rains of Castamere]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

[[Bran Stark]], [[Hodor]], [[Summer]], [[Jojen Reed]] and [[Meera Reed]] arrive at the Nightfort and camp in the chamber containing the well. Bran tells his friends the story of the [[rat cook]], a former cook at the Nightfort who was insulted by a king who stayed at the castle. He killed the king's son and served his flesh to his father inside a pie. The gods, furious at this insult to the [[Guest right|ancient laws of hospitality]], turned the cook into a white rat cursed to feed on its own offspring forever.

The group then encounter Samwell Tarly and Gilly, who show them how to leave the castle via the tunnel.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Mhysa]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
